Amethyst

World:
AmethystOre - Amethyst
Aluminum - Bauxite - cans, utencils, good conductor, transmission lines, 
Copper - chalcopyrite, Chalcocite, Bornite, covellite, tetrahedrite, enargite - wiring and motor, machinery and construction, 
Zinc - sphalerite - galvanize, brass, nickel silver and aluminium solder.
Silver - argentite (Ag2S), chlorargyrite ("horn silver," AgCl), and galena - solder electrical contacts and batteries, printed circuits
Silicon from quartz(silica)
Tin - coat metal to prevent corrosion
Lead - car batteries, pigments, ammunition, cable sheathing, radiation protection
Lithium - from brine - rechargable batteries, A magnesium-lithium alloy is used for armour plating. Aluminium-lithium alloys are used in aircraft, bicycle frames and high-speed trains.
nickel - steel alloy - resist corrosion, stainless steel, boat propeller shafts and turbine blades., nickel-cadmium batteries and nickel-metal hydride batteries
sulphur - from gas and oil - gunpowder, sulfuric acid

Iron - steel, pipes valves and pumps
Stainless steel is very resistant to corrosion. It contains at least 10.5% chromium. Other metals such as nickel, molybdenum, titanium and copper are added to enhance its strength and workability. It is used in architecture, bearings, cutlery, surgical instruments and jewellery.
Gold - electroplate electric component, circuits, coat copper components, 

