Steelmaking:

blast furnace => iron ore, coke(also pet coke), and limestone. Charcoal and anthracite to produce pig iron

Refractory lined container, ladle
magnesium added, exothermic to reduct sulfur inpurities
de-silicon and phosphorous with iron oxide(mill scale) and lime

filling the furnace => charging 1/5 steel scrap,  4% C, 0.2–0.8% Si, 0.08%–0.18% P, and 0.01–0.04% S

water cooled lance blowes oxygen, igniting carbon impurities and raise temperature to 1700 cel -> melts scrap
Fluxes (burnt lime or dolomite) are fed into the vessel to form slag, absorb impurities
typical =  0.3–0.6% C, 0.05–0.1% Mn, 0.01–0.03% Si, 0.01–0.03% S and P.

poured in to ladle and alloy

Basic Oxygen Furnace 
manganese, nickel, chromium and vanadium are added to produce steel

electric arc furnace


7yh6
method to purify aluminum
Bayer process https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayer_process
wash bauxite with NaOH at 175 cel under pressure, convert aluminum oxide to sodium aluminate produce water as well
rotary sand trap to filter out red mud with flocculant
water + seed with AlOH3 to produce AlOH3 crystal and NaOH
heat to 980 cel, decompose to aluminum oxide and water

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hall–Héroult_process
to smelt aluminum
dissolve in molten cryolite, Na3AlF6 lower melting point and improve conductivity

cryolite, alumina and aluminium fluoride is electrolyzed by passing low voltage (3-5V) direct current through it.

deposited at the cathode while the oxygen from the alumina combines with carbon from the anode to produce carbon dioxide

rolling machine






